adjectives.description: unincorporate (comparative more unincorporate, superlative most unincorporate)

verbs.description: unincorporate (third-person singular simple present unincorporates, present participle unincorporating, simple past and past participle unincorporated)

entries.meaning: To undo or remove the incorporation of.
examples: Unincorporating doesn't trigger a pension break in this situation: A doctor liquidated his corporation and terminated its pension coverage, taking lump-sum payout. But he continued practicing as a sole proprietor at the same address ...
